(4, 'Individual Assignment: Applied User Interface Design Case Study', '<h1 dir=\"ltr\"><b><font size=\"5\" color=\"#000000\">Individual Assignment: Applied User Interface Design Case Study</font></b></h1><h3 dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\"><br></font></h3><h2 dir=\"ltr\"></h2><h2 dir=\"ltr\"><b><font size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\">Case Study Instructions</font></b></h2><div><b><font size=\"4\" color=\"#000000\"><br></font></b></div><h3 dir=\"ltr\"><b><font color=\"#000000\">Step 1 — Choose Two Real Interfaces (15 marks)</font></b></h3><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\">Select&nbsp;any two&nbsp;digital interfaces you use frequently — for example:</font></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\"><br></font></p><ul><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><font color=\"#000000\">A&nbsp;mobile banking app&nbsp;(e.g., BK App, MoMo, EcoCash, PayPal)<br><br></font></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><font color=\"#000000\">A&nbsp;learning platform&nbsp;(e.g., Google Classroom, Moodle, Coursera)<br><br></font></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><font color=\"#000000\">A&nbsp;social or utility app&nbsp;(e.g., Instagram, WhatsApp, Spotify, Gmail)<br><br></font></p></li></ul><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\">You must analyze&nbsp;two different UI styles&nbsp;— for instance, one using&nbsp;Material Design&nbsp;and another using&nbsp;Flat or Neumorphic&nbsp;style.</font></p><font color=\"#000000\"><br></font><h3 dir=\"ltr\"><b><font color=\"#000000\">Step 2 — Deep UI Element Analysis (20 marks)</font></b></h3><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\">For each interface:</font></p><ol><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><font color=\"#000000\">Identify and categorize at least&nbsp;8–10 key UI elements&nbsp;into:<br><br></font></p></li><ul><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"2\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><font color=\"#000000\">Input elements<br><br></font></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"2\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><font color=\"#000000\">Output/display elements<br><br></font></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"2\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><font color=\"#000000\">Helper/structural elements<br><br></font></p></li></ul><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><font color=\"#000000\">Create a&nbsp;table or diagram&nbsp;showing each element, its purpose, and whether it follows good design principles.<br><br></font></p></li></ol><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\">Example format:</font></p><div dir=\"ltr\" align=\"left\"><table><colgroup><col width=\"104\"><col width=\"56\"><col width=\"147\"><col width=\"150\"><col width=\"168\"></colgroup><tbody><tr><td><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\">UI Element</font></p></td><td><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\">Type</font></p></td><td><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\">Purpose</font></p></td><td><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\">Good Design Practice?</font></p></td><td><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\">Notes</font></p></td></tr><tr><td><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\">Login Button</font></p></td><td><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\">Input</font></p></td><td><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\">Submits credentials</font></p></td><td><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\">?</font></p></td><td><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\">Clear label, strong contrast</font></p></td></tr><tr><td><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\">Navigation Bar</font></p></td><td><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\">Helper</font></p></td><td><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\">Moves between screens</font></p></td><td><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\">?</font></p></td><td><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\">Too many options, cluttered</font></p></td></tr></tbody></table></div><font color=\"#000000\"><br></font><h3 dir=\"ltr\"><b><font color=\"#000000\">Step 3 — Principles Evaluation (20 marks)</font></b></h3><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\">For each interface, analyze how well it follows&nbsp;UI design principles:</font></p><ul><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><font color=\"#000000\">Hierarchy<br><br></font></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><font color=\"#000000\">Consistency<br><br></font></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><font color=\"#000000\">Contrast<br><br></font></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><font color=\"#000000\">Alignment<br><br></font></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><font color=\"#000000\">Proximity<br><br></font></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><font color=\"#000000\">Accessibility<br><br></font></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><font color=\"#000000\">Feedback</font></p></li></ul><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\">Give&nbsp;specific examples&nbsp;(screenshots allowed) and explain&nbsp;how&nbsp;each principle is applied or violated.</font></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\">Example:</font></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\">The “Send” button in WhatsApp uses color contrast (green) to indicate the primary action, showing strong hierarchy and accessibility.</font></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\"><br></font></p><h3 dir=\"ltr\"><b><font color=\"#000000\">Step 4 — Design Style Analysis (15 marks)</font></b></h3><div><b><font color=\"#000000\"><br></font></b></div><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\">Compare the&nbsp;two design styles&nbsp;you studied:</font></p><ol><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><font color=\"#000000\">Identify which uses&nbsp;Flat,&nbsp;Material, or&nbsp;Neumorphic&nbsp;design.<br><br></font></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><font color=\"#000000\">Explain how these styles affect usability, loading time, and visual clarity.<br><br></font></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><font color=\"#000000\">Discuss which one you think is&nbsp;more user-friendly&nbsp;and why.<br><br></font></p></li></ol><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\">Use references (e.g., from Figma, UXPin, or Google Material Design guidelines).</font></p><font color=\"#000000\"><br></font><h3 dir=\"ltr\"></h3><h3 dir=\"ltr\"><b><font color=\"#000000\">Step 5 — Redesign Challenge (20 marks)</font></b></h3><div><b><font color=\"#000000\"><br></font></b></div><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\">Pick&nbsp;one&nbsp;of the two apps and&nbsp;redesign one problematic screen.</font></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\">You must:</font></p><ol><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><font color=\"#000000\">Identify&nbsp;three usability issues&nbsp;(poor contrast, unclear buttons, bad feedback, etc.).<br><br></font></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><font color=\"#000000\">Propose an improved design (you can sketch, wireframe, or describe).<br><br></font></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><font color=\"#000000\">Justify every change with&nbsp;design principles.<br><br></font></p></li></ol><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\">Example justification:</font></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\">I increased button size and color contrast to improve accessibility for users with visual impairments (WCAG principle).</font></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\"><br></font></p><h3 dir=\"ltr\"><b><font color=\"#000000\">Step 6 — Reflection &amp; Accessibility Review (10 marks)</font></b></h3><div><b><font color=\"#000000\"><br></font></b></div><p dir=\"ltr\"><font color=\"#000000\">In one page:</font></p><ul><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><font color=\"#000000\">Reflect on&nbsp;what you learned&nbsp;about user perception, accessibility, and feedback.<br><br></font></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><font color=\"#000000\">Discuss how designing for&nbsp;disabilities&nbsp;changes your thinking about UI.<br><br></font></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><font color=\"#000000\">Suggest one way your redesigned screen could be inclusive for all users.<br><br></font></p></li></ul><h3 dir=\"ltr\"><b><font color=\"#000000\">Submission Details</font></b></h3><ul><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><font color=\"#000000\">Format: PDF or Word document (3–6 pages max)<br></font></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><font color=\"#000000\">Include your name, student ID, and screenshots (if used).</font></p></li></ul>', '2025-10-23 23:30:00', 100, 'both', NULL, NULL, 2, 1, 'published', '2025-10-22 15:22:39', '2025-10-22 15:26:58'),
(5, 'THEORETICAL TEST', '<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-19f801e1-7fff-f9b7-f9ca-26dfece24042\"><h1 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size: inherit;\"><b>Section 1: Understanding Web Development (15 marks)</b></span></h1><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"\">Answer any three (3) questions. Each question carries 5 marks.</p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"\"><br></p><ol style=\"\"><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">1. Web development involves several interconnected layers.<br> a) Briefly describe the role of HTML, CSS, and JavaScript in modern web development.<br> b) Analyze how these three interact during page rendering in a browser.<br><br></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">2. Evaluate the impact of web ergonomics on user satisfaction.<br> a) Explain what web ergonomics means in practice.<br> b) Propose two ergonomic design choices you would apply to improve usability on a government information website.<br><br></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">3. Browsers are not only viewers but also processors of web content.<br> a) Describe what happens after a user enters a URL and presses Enter.<br> b) Explain how the DOM, CSSOM, and render tree interact to produce the visual output.<br><br></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">4. Different browsers may display the same page differently.<br> Discuss the main factors that cause cross-browser inconsistencies and propose two practical methods to minimize them.<br><br></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">5. Explain the importance of responsive web design in today’s multi-device environment.<br> Include at least two CSS or design techniques that make a page responsive.<br><br></p></li></ol><h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"\"></h2><h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"\"><b>Section 2: Understanding HTML (15 marks)</b></h2><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"\">Answer any three (3) questions. Each question carries 5 marks.</p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"\"><br></p><ol style=\"\"><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">6. Analyze the difference between semantic HTML and non-semantic HTML.<br> Why is semantic structure crucial for accessibility and SEO? Give at least two examples of semantic tags and their correct usage.</p></li></ol><br><ol start=\"2\" style=\"\"><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">7. Forms are essential for collecting user data.<br> a) Explain the purpose of key attributes such as action, method, name, and required.<br> b) Suggest improvements to this form snippet:<br><br> &lt;form&gt;</p></li></ol><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"\">&lt;input placeholder=\"Enter name\"&gt;</p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\">	</span><span class=\"Apple-tab-span\">	</span>&lt;button&gt;Send&lt;/button&gt;</p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;/form&gt;</p><ol start=\"3\" style=\"\"><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Examine the concept of nesting and hierarchy in HTML.<br> Why does proper nesting matter for both design layout and browser parsing? Illustrate your answer with a valid code example.</p></li></ol><br><ol start=\"4\" style=\"\"><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">8. Evaluate how HTML attributes (both global and tag-specific) enhance functionality and interactivity of web pages.<br> Provide examples to support your argument.</p></li></ol><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"\"></p><br><ol start=\"5\" style=\"\"><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">9. Given the following HTML snippet, identify and correct at least three semantic or structural errors:</p></li></ol><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;body&gt;</p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;div&gt;</p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;h5&gt;Main Title&lt;/h1&gt;</p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;This page explains HTML.&lt;/strong&gt;</p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;img alt=Campus src=\"campus.jpg\"&gt;</p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;/section&gt;</p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"\">&lt;/body&gt;</p><br><br><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"\"><b>Section 3: Understanding CSS (20 marks)</b></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"\">Answer any four (4) questions. Each question carries 5 marks.</p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"\"><br></p><ol style=\"\"><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">10. Compare and contrast the three main methods of applying CSS (inline, internal, and external).<br> Which method is most maintainable for large-scale projects and why?<br><br></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">11. Analyze how the CSS Box Model affects layout design.<br> a) Define each component (content, padding, border, margin).<br> b) Describe a scenario where misunderstanding the box model could distort a page’s layout.<br><br></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">12. Flexbox and Grid are modern layout tools.<br> a) Discuss the key differences between Flexbox and Grid.<br> b) Explain when each is more appropriate to use.<br><br></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">13. Evaluate the role of media queries in responsive design.<br> Provide an example CSS snippet that changes the layout of a page when the viewport width exceeds 768px.<br><br></p></li></ol><br><ol start=\"5\" style=\"\"><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\" style=\"\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">14. Examine the impact of CSS specificity on debugging and maintenance.<br> Provide an example of conflicting CSS rules and explain which one the browser applies and why.<br><br></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\" style=\"\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"\">15. Consider the principle of separation of concerns in web design.<br> a) Explain how CSS contributes to this principle.<br> b) Discuss how violating it (e.g., through inline styling) can affect collaboration and scalability.</p></li></ol></span>', '2025-10-27 11:55:00', 100, 'both', NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 'completed', '2025-10-27 09:10:17', '2025-10-27 10:05:28');
